kbuild: fix kernel 4.4 module build with GNU make >= 4.4

Two problems building this driver out-of-tree (make -C $KDIR M=...) with
GNU make 4.4+:

1. The bare `export` (export-all-variables) directive poisons the recursive
   kbuild sub-make parse under make 4.4+, aborting with:
       scripts/Makefile.lib:393: *** prerequisites cannot be defined in recipes.
   Comment it out (an explicit `export WIFI_PROJ_DIR` remains just above).

2. $(PWD) resolves to the *kernel* build dir under `make -C $KDIR`, not the
   driver source tree, so:
     - the driver .config (installed by the package PRE_CONFIGURE hook) was
       never read, and
     - hal_apollo/ (a separate sub-make) re-includes $(WIFI_PROJ_DIR)/.config,
       which pointed at the kernel dir -> CONFIG_ATBM_SDIO_BUS was unset ->
       SDIO_BUS/-DSDIO_BUS missing -> fwio.c fails with DOWNLOAD_ITCM_ADDR,
       DOWNLOAD_BLOCK_SIZE, ALTOBEAM_WIFI_HDR_FLAG undeclared.
   Use $(src) (the module source dir kbuild sets) for both.

Verified: builds hal_apollo/atbm6031.ko clean against linux 4.4.94 with
GNU make 4.4.1.

Signed-off-by: thingino

--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -3,7 +3,7 @@
 #CONFIG_ATBM601x: 1T1R 80211b/g/n, HT20
 #if yout want to change .conf ,please do make menuconfig in current path
 ############################################################################
--include $(PWD)/.config
+-include $(src)/.config
 ############################################################################
 #
 #	The Follow Code Of The Makefile Should Not Be Changed
@@ -12,8 +12,8 @@
 PWD:=$(shell pwd)
 WIFI_INSTALL_DIR := $(PWD)/driver_install

-export WIFI_PROJ_DIR=$(PWD)
-export
+export WIFI_PROJ_DIR=$(src)
+#export # export-all breaks kbuild sub-make parse with GNU make >= 4.4
 -include $(src)/Makefile.build.kernel

 export DRIVER_PATH ?= $(PWD)
